The paper proposes a method for interpreting and accelerating convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV). The method involves controlling the network architecture and identifying activated filters, which are key components of deep learning models (cs.LG). The paper also mentions maximizing mutual information, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses limiting the outputs of filters during training, which is a technique used in neural network optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions adversarial attacks, which are a common topic in natural language processing and computer vision research (cs.CL).
